==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''daz'', originally [[dat]]
===Article===
{{German definite article}}
'''das'''
*[[the]] (Nominative singular neuter of the [[definite article]]. See ''[[der]]'').

===Relative pronoun===
'''das'''
#[[who]], [[that]] (In a subordinate clause, indicates a person or thing referenced in the main clause. Used with neuter singular referents).
#: Ich kenne ein Mädchen, ''das'' das kann: I know a girl ''who'' can do that.

